The '''Corellian Exclusion Zone''' was a zone in the space surrounding [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] during the [[Second Galactic Civil War]] established during [[Blockade of Corellia]] in [[40 ABY/Legends|40 ABY]].
After [[Battle of Tralus (Second Galactic Civil War)|occupation]] of [[Tralus/Legends|Tralus]] by [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances|Galactic Alliance]] failed, this imposed blockade only enraged the inhabitants of the [[Corellian system/Legends|Corellian system]] and encouraged more systems to join the later formed [[Confederation]].

During the blockade, however, the Galactic Alliance [[Galactic Alliance Defense Fleet|military forces]] were keeping their heavy presence noticed by denying any ship to leave or travel to the planet which thus became totally isolated.
This was mainly for keeping food and material away from the [[Orbital Industrial Zone|orbital factories]], forcing the Corellian [[Five Worlds|government]] to surrender. The blockade also affected the [[CEC shipyards|shipyards]] of the [[Corellian Engineering Corporation/Legends|Corellian Engineering Corporation]] very badly, which could get disastrous effects on Corellia. Only ships of the Galactic Alliance military, or civil ships with special codes, could travel through the exclusion zone without taking the risk of being shot down.

The Corellian Exclusion Zone was dismissed after fleets from [[Commenor/Legends|Commenor]] and [[Bothawui/Legends|Bothawui]] helped Corellian military forces to overwhelm the Alliance blockade at the [[Battle of Corellia (Second Galactic Civil War)|Battle of Corellia]].

